{"id":3388259141,"url":"http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3622/3388259141_4a416d08d6.jpg","path":"9fa/8e5/9fa8e555248bbff159b4e513739f4.jpg","date":"2008-03-29","year":2008,"month":3,"lon":-99.80189,"lat":30.922714,"tags":"abandoned,fort,menard,menard+county,mlhradio,presidio,presidio+san+saba,ruins,san+saba,san+saba+presidio,texas,texas+centennial","S2CellId":"12a3fc0000000000","result":685,"accuracy":0.08238565,"title":"presidiosansaba30","description":"Presidio+San+Saba%2C+Menard+County%2C+Texas.++One+of+the+more+interesting+-+and+least+known+-+relics+of+Texas%27+Spanish+past.++The+ruins+of+the+San+Saba+Presidio+can+be+found+on+the+outskirts+of+Menard%2C+at+the+edge+of+the+town%27s+golf+course+and+country+club.%0A%0AThe+Presidio+%28formally+known+as+Presidio+San+Luis+de+las+Amarillas%29+was+constructed+in+1757%2C+primarily+to+serve+as+protection+to+the+nearby+Mission+San+Saba+a+few+miles+downriver.++The+missionaries+went+about+doing+what+missionaries+do+-+converting+the+%27heathen%2C+godless+savages%27+also+known+as+the+local+Lipan+Apache.++But+by+befriending+the+Apache%2C+the+Spaniards+made+enemies+of+several+more+powerful+tribes+to+the+north+and+west+-+these+Nortenos+swept+down+in+an+army+of+a+couple+thousand+warriors+and+destroyed+both+the+mission+and+presidio+less+than+a+year+later.%0A%0AThe+mission+was+never+rebuilt%2C+and+soon+faded+into+memory+and+then+into+myth+%28the+exact+location+was+not+re-discovered+until+recently%29%2C+but+the+fort+was+promptly+rebuilt%2C+primarily+on+dreams+of+silver+mines.++But+when+that+proved+unprofitable%2C+the+presidio+was+permanently+abandoned+in+1772.%0A%0AFast+forward+to+1936%2C+when+the+Texas+Centennial+Commission+decided+it+would+be+a+good+idea+to+rebuild+the+fort.++And+so%2C+for+the+next+year%2C+they+rebuilt+about+a+quarter+of+the+original+presidio+structure+--+and+they+did+it+*badly*.++It+is+these+crumbling+ruins+that+you+find+when+you+visit+the+site+-+broken+stone+walls%2C+scattered+remnants+of+rooms%2C+huge+cracks+in+the+structures%2C+threatening+to+fall+over+in+a+strong+wind.++Despite+the+historical+interest%2C+the+site+is+not+part+of+the+state+parks+or+historical+system+-+instead+it+has+fallen+into+an+almost+complete+state+of+disrepair+under+the+guardianship+of+the+town+of+Menard.++There+have+been+recent+excavations+at+the+%27lost%27+mission%2C+and+renewed+interest+in+preserving+the+presidio+and+mission+locations%2C+which+may+come+to+fruition+in+the+next+few+years.%0A%0AThis+was+just+a+quick+visit+for+me%2C+while+driving+home+from+Fort+McKavett+on+March+29%2C+2008.++For+more+information%3A%0A%0A%3Ca+href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.texasbeyondhistory.net%2Fpresidio%2Findex.html%22%3ETexas+Beyond+History+website%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%3Ca+href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.swco.ttu.edu%2Fmedieval%2FPresidio.html%22%3ETexas+Tech+University+website%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%3Ca+href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Frdenney.bizland.com%2FTexasHistory%2FSan+Saba%2Fsan_saba_presidio_and_mission.htm%22%3ETexas+History+Blog%3C%2Fa%3E"}
